ida-adreno-qrisc
================

ISA and PM4 packet definitions are generated from Mesa 3D:

  https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/mesa/mesa

Files used at generation time to produce `common/qrisc_isa_tables.py`:

  src/freedreno/qrisc/qrisc.xml
  src/freedreno/registers/adreno/adreno_control_regs.xml
  src/freedreno/registers/adreno/adreno_pm4.xml

These are MIT-licensed, copyright Google, Inc.; Valve Corporation; Rob Clark;
and other Mesa contributors, per the Mesa repository.

The generator (`gen/qrisc_isa_gen.py`) reuses Mesa's `isa.py` parser
(`src/compiler/isaspec/isa.py`, MIT, copyright Google) at generation time. No
Mesa code or data is required at runtime.

Pinned Mesa commit at release:
  4bf8fd5121122abd87aafb31e43bbbe9e3d2e921 (main, 2026-06-22)

Test fixtures `fixtures/qrisc_test*.fw` and `fixtures/qrisc_test*.asm` are
reproduced from Mesa's `src/freedreno/tests/` and remain under their original
license.

